<br>
I mean, c'mon.  Sure, when that really nice melee item drops, I *really* want to roll on them because hell, I need pp too.   It used to happen in seb a lot, and just a lot in general.   As a general rule, a lot more Melee stuff drops then Caster stuff.<br>
<br>
But I didn't roll, unless everyone in the group was like &quot;Don't need.&quot;   In this case, everyone rolls.<br>
<br>
The idea that &quot;xyz melee does as much work here as anyone&quot; is moot.   Yea, they are putting in their effort, but they are getting rewarded - exp.<br>
<br>
When a pure melee levels from 60 - 65, they get more disciplines, more hit points, more AA things to do.   When a caster levels from 60-65, sure, we have some more AA's, but the only thing that makes us more powerful is spells.<br>
<br>
I've never had a melee roll on a parchment in my group.  And I have never had a caster roll on an item that a melee can use.  I just hope this stays the case wherever I group; I don't want to police the group and I don't want melees to think that we don't appreciate their abilities.<br>
<br>
