<br>
Here's how that works for parchments:<br>
<br>
Parchment drops, 60+ casters /random to see who gets it.  Once you get a parchment, you're done unless you manage to get more parchments than casters.  At the end of the night, turn them in.  If you get a duplicate, those are randomed to anyone who didn't get anything.  60s roll to give them a reason to hit 61.  Being 61 with no spells sucks.<br>
<br>
Granted, this probably won't work for pickup groups.  For that, I'd suggest the same rule, but more likely, the 57 cleric will want to roll.  I'd let the 62 warrior roll if the 57 cleric is going to roll.  Money is money if you can't use the item. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cbreaker1212>CBreaker1212</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 5:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: melees rolling on parchments</span><hr size=1> Not saying a 57 caster should be getting parchments, but with pop you must admit that it's a hell of a lot easier to get from 57 to 61 now.   You could do it in a week of steady grouping. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nordochump>NordoChump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 6:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: melees rolling on parchments</span><hr size=1> How fast are YOU getting AA?  59 is 5 AA of exp, 58 and 60 are about 3 each.  If you can get 11 AA in one week, you're playing all the time.  You aren't going to be level 57 to begin with.  And good luck getting a group at 57 all week. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/b