<br>
Melee's rolling on parchments is dumb.  Before PoP, I lvled in seb almost exclusively.  Whenever RBG's drop, the melees call NBG on it; before luclin came out it was worse because alot of melee's actually used the gear that drops down there, so 90% of the time melees would be getting everything, and some clerics would try to take ALL the gems (a cleric only needs like one-two extra &quot;good&quot; gem(s) to cover symbol costs) Now its my turn to get the loot.  PoP has brought alot of great stuff for casters to the table, loot is part of it.  <br>
<br>
Another thing that ticks me off is low lvl people rolling on parchments.  I was grouped with a 54 cleric the other day that claimed he already had most of his 61-62 spells and had gotten duplicate copies of virtue and sold it for 40k!  I've got THREE 61 turn-in spells, and thats it!  He got pretty pissed off when I told him he couldn't roll on a parchment that dropped.  I just say, &quot;look man, if you've already got most of your 61-62 spells at 54 and i've got 3 at 61, that's screwed up.  Your probibly going to get a duplicate and just sell it!  Hell I might as well let the warrior roll!&quot;.  Needless to say, I took the parchment.<br>
<br>
It's just B.S. what some poeple try to pull.  The only time I'll let low level people roll on parchments is if i'm the ONLY one in the group 61+ and it's a caster heavy group, and only because it would feel kinda odd taking ALL the loot =P.<br>
<br>
Anyways I'm done ranting heh...my last comment (i'm ganna get flamed for this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ):<br>
<br>
Rationalising melee's looting parchments is like rationalising gun control.  Once you look through all the facts, it just doesn't make sense. <p>Tiiden VandorGriffin<br>
