 pp to get the spells or to roll for parchments..shouldn't they be rewarded for spending more time playing...I keep telling myself I won't read these rants anymore but I can't resist beating on this bizarre concept...If it's not a no-drop item then anyone who wants to roll should be able to...they helped kill the mob too and if we all did that then the law of avgs would have me trading  you for the part I need and vice versa...in fact we even have a thing called money to help facilitate that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#333333>(12/10/02 8:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: just make sure you know loot rules before you join a gro</span><hr size=1> I agree... know the rules when you join.<br>
